    act_title: 'Mr. Successful.',
    producers: 'Douglas McGray',
    act_description:
     'Anthony Pico was a foster kid for most of his life. His mother was a crack addict who abandoned him, and he bounced around from house to house, relative to relative. But unlike a lot of foster kids, he had an amazing ability to talk about his life eloquently. He started getting invited to child welfare conferences, presenting to social workers and politicians and bureaucrats about problems with the foster care system. He got so good at it that he turned into a professional foster kid. Reporter Doug McGray tells Anthony\'s story. (20 minutes)Doug McGray is a fellow at the New America Foundation.',
